    "rich_text_KUaUxq": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_pM9EKt": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Aidan is a floral designer and event stylist based in Vancouver, BC. She builds atmospheric floral installations and arrangements for events, businesses, and homes. She’s the girl who falls in love with every stem she sees. The one lagging behind on a walk to photograph the plants, showing you a tiny detail of a leaf, pulling over the car to forage something on the side of the road, and generally being sentimental about beautiful things. Working with flowers and plants is a source of play, creativity, and meditation for her. The natural world and its many cycles is where she looks for inspiration. </p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_pM9EKt"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "center",
        "content_alignment": "center",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 0,
        "padding_bottom": 36
      }
    },
    "image_with_text_t6KzFw": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CcwiLn": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><a href=\"https://www.thingsfromgardens.com/\">Things From Gardens</a> is named after how she started arranging flowers: gathering bits from around her neighbourhood and experimenting with how to style them. Starting this way taught her to find beauty in unusual things and made her resourceful in where she looked for materials.</p><p></p><p>Before starting her business, Aidan worked in tech and took vacation days to work on floral projects. In 2023 she decided to follow her true passions and connect to people through the joy of flowers, so she quit my corporate job and started working for herself. Today, she loves to bring concepts to life in large and small scale projects and teach workshops.</p><p></p><p>If you want to learn more about her work and support <a href=\"https://www.thingsfromgardens.com/\">Things From Gardens</a>, join her on IG <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/things_from_gardens/\">@things_from_gardens</a>. We spent the morning with Aidan in her studio to hear more about the story behind <a href=\"https://www.thingsfromgardens.com/\">Things From Gardens</a>. Read the full interview below.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_CcwiLn"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/VALENTINE_ACTIVATION-5046.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "small",
        "layout": "image_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "middle",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
