    "image_with_text_c4jGUN": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_WTVxJJ": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h3>Q: What’s your favourite childhood snack?</h3><p>A: Two things came to mind. One, I loved watching TV and eating <a href=\"https://www.wholesaleclub.ca/en/crispers-all-dressed-crackers-baked-snacks\">all dressed Crispers</a>. So random but so nostalgic. My mom blow drying my hair after a bath and eating all dressed Crispers while watching TV. The second is sneaking a bunch of rice crispies that my bubbe would make me as a kid while playing the Sims and finishing a whole bag of rice crispies that was supposed to last us a week. </p><h3>Q: How would you describe your style?</h3><p>A: My style has changed a lot since I have started this business because I’m often getting ready a lot to go to the studio everyday and working with flowers is very physical and manual work. So, I think I would describe my style now as pragmatic but I always try to look cute. I try getting dressed for the studio everyday even if I am the only person I am going to see. I really like wearing clothes that are comfortable. I like wearing clothes that I can move in really easily but I also like things that have a little bit of a classic touch with new proportions, which I am wearing right now. Can’t go wrong with a button down shirt, I’d wear a button down shirt every single day. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
